The paper discusses modifications to the gradient boosted decision trees algorithm, which is commonly used in machine learning and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses memory usage and histogram techniques, which are relevant to data structures and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely sub-category. The modifications to the algorithm are aimed at improving accuracy, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the experiments conducted in the paper involve large datasets, which is relevant to data mining (cs.DM).
